de.esoco.lib.model

Interface DataProvider<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataProvider, ListDataProvider

    public interface DataProvider<T>
    An interface for objects that provide access to indexed data.

    • Method Summary

      • of

        Returns a new data provider that contains a certain collection of data objects.

        Returns:
        The new data provider

      • getData

        java.util.Collection<T> getData(int nStart,
                                int nCount)
        Returns a subset of data objects from this provider. If less data then requested is available the returned collection may contain less elements then nCount. It may even be empty but it will never be NULL.
        Parameters:
        nStart - The starting index of the first data object to return
        nCount - The number of data objects to return
        Returns:
        A collection of data objects (may be empty but will never be NULL)

      • size

        int size()
        Returns the number of data objects that are available from this provider.
        Returns:
        The count of available data objects
